m><span class=title> cleric tactics - interested in your opinion</span><hr size=1> There being several clerics in the guild I am curious about their opinions.  I am also interested in the reaction of warriors to this situation.<br>
<br>
Bruloff (34 cleric) was in a group the other day not long after getting Sup heal.   Sup heal is about 17% more efficient mana wise than greater heal, assuming the target is not over healed (you wait until the target's health is down sufficiently to get all the healing applied.)   Since sup heal does 583 hp heal, this means that level 30ish warriors, even if buffed to 1500 hps or so, must be down over 2 bubbles to get the advantage of sup heal.<br>
<br>
So I announced to the backup healer and the warrior who was main assist not to panic until the main assist was below 50% health, as I planned to use sup heal as the main healing option.<br>
<br>
We had 2 warriors in the group.  The main assist started to complain at once that this was too dangerous.  If she ran into a goon, she would need near full health to run to zone.  After hearing this for a while, I gave the healing over to another member of the group and stated I would nuke - which was fine with me and seemed to keep everyone calm. <br>
<br>
My other high char is a 42 warrior.  Personally having my health go low doesnt bother me while fighting as long as I am getting regular messages from the cleric that suggest they arent LD.  Personally I like to see the cleric chat a lot - even if it is just stating mana every 10%.  But my survivability while pulling depends almost entirely on one thing - SoW.  In my opinion for example in OT, if smacked by a goon if I have 50% health and SoW I will survive - with 100% health and no SoW I won't.<br>
<br>
Anyway I wonder what opinions you healers and tanks have.<br>
<br>
Bruloff/Macbruson<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/bemarr80492.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kogginnstormkoffinn>Kogginn Stormkoffinn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://championsofkaos.iwarp.com/members/none.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fearless Leader and Webmaster</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#993300>(1/6/02 5:38:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/femarr80492frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://cofk.com/members/kogg.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: cleric tactics - interested in your opinion</span><hr size=1> I tend to agree Bru.<br>
<br>
As you may have noticed, I am not a big fan of waiting too long to heal.<br>
<br>
I tend to heal casters if they lose 1 bub or more of thier HP, as soon as i can.<br>
Tanks after losing more than 2 (3 if I am LOM).<br>
<br>
There are always exceptions...  Like if someone loses three bubbles of health in a 2 second period.  <br>
<br>
Also take into account that Greater heal at your level is still faster than Sup heal...  So It may be worth it to Greater THEN Super...  I have that issue arise frequently except I use exclusively Superior healing and Celestial healing.<br>
<br>
But it truly does depend on the situation.<br>
<br>
