Dwarven Cleric of Brell Sirilis - Level 45</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/uzoldarf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zoldarf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#993300>(1/7/02 1:19:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/femarr80492frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: cleric tactics - interested in your opinion</span><hr size=1> I don't even notice my health bar until it's below 2 bubbles... I get concerned around 1 bubble.  The key to keeping your tanks happy is to let them know what's going on.  This means spam, and lots of it... we are less likely to panic if we know a heal is being cast, even if we're very low on health.  Macros macros macros.<br>
<br>
The best spam I've seen was from some random cleric I grouped with in DL.  It was something like this:<br>
<br>
Casting Superior Heal on Zoldarf (640hp, cast time 6 sec)<br>
<br>
It was nice to know how long it would be before the heal landed.   Back then you didn't know how much you'd been healed for either, so this information was nice too.<br>
<br>
-Zoldarf <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/ustyrowhatever.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Styrowhatever</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#993300>(1/7/02 6:16:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/femarr80492frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://bindpoint.com/images/styrogur_tux_small.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: cleric tactics - interested in your opinion</span><hr size=1> Here's Styrona's input:<br>
<br>
Since I was pretty much dirt-poor until level 39, I didn't have much wisdom gear. (Or any other good gear--I was still using a WOODEN SHIELD at level 41.) That meant that I had to use my mana as efficiently as possible, and I still have a tendency to do that, as anyone who has watched me cast Complete Healing on Styrogur when he's almost dead can attest.<br>
<br>
So, when I got Superior Healing, I tried to make sure it counted. I'd try to time my heals to that tanks would end up with over 80% but just under 100% health. (hitting 100% meant wasted mana.) If I'm doing my job right, it will be a rare case where the tank would have lived if I had just spent the mana to get him to 100%. It's much more likely that, by saving mana, I may save someone's life when I might otherwise have been OOM.<br>
<br>
For INT casters, I kept Greater Healing memmed, and always tried to get them to 100%. (If they ended up barely under I would let natural regen finish it off. Less than 95% or so, I'd spend the mana to heal them the rest of the way.) For other healing classes, I'd get them up above 80%, and figure if they wanted to top off they could do it themselves.<br>
<br>
Basically, and I believe Styrogur will agree with me on this, any sowed tank in OT who's not willing to go out and pull when he's at 40% is a cockatrice--I mean, a chicken. <p>Styrogur (Ogre Warrior)<BR>Styrona Nightingale (High Elf Cleric)<BR>Styrogyro Mindwarper (Erudite Enchanter)<BR>Styrosham (Ogre Shaman)<BR>Styrog (Dwarf Rogue)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Kehli</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#993300>(1/7/02 8:22:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/femarr80492frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Int caster here</span><hr size=1> For me personally, if I am taking any damage at all, it mean I have generated aggro, prob by mezzing or stunning, and that aggro prob wont go away anytime soon.<br>
<br>
In other words, if I take a bub of damage, I will die without a fast heal. They want me dead. Period. <br>
<br>
Its a strange symbiosis, the cleric chanter relationship - the chanter needs the cleric to stay alive, the cleric needs the chanter to control the mobs so they can keep the team alive.  If the chanter or the cleric dies, the group is often in serious peril.  Many times I have run into the fray to try and stun a mob off Kog, or mez a mob uder attack, just to generate the very aggro that may kill me, in order to give kog the precious seconds to save our tank.<br>
<br>
I would far sooner have Kog rez me, than lose another teammate that could have been saved - BUT - if I die, I cant control the mobs.<br>
<br>
Veeeery complex this is. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/ulogicalentity.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LogicalEntity</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#993300>(1/8/02 12:49:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/femarr80492frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> INT Caster (magician)</span><hr size=1> Most of the time this doesn't happen ... but every once in a while you come across a cleric that will heal a pet! Which is very much appreciated by me, and i'm sure all mages alike. Especially in a group where a pet is taking a lot of damage. Summoning these pets take a lot of mana! I wish Verant would do some special life meter bar for our pets ... maybe like put a &quot;blue bar&quot; inside our health bar for the pets or something ... kinda like how the &quot;exp bar works&quot; cuz there's no way for others to select the stupid pet without clicking on it. Oh well.<br>
<br>
