-Zoldarf <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/undrokk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ndrokk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Vice President Critterwacker</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#993300>(1/23/02 5:49:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/femarr80492frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://warmancomputers.iwarp.com/eqme.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Cleric tactics</span><hr size=1> <br>
Upper level Clerics have many options for excellent strategies. Having never played a cleric, I can only offer my magely observations.<br>
<br>
Aamadar chain cast a group heal on us at a Naggy raid. It worked, we all survived. An excellent tactic which I had not experienced before.<br>
<br>
I have heard of clerics casting celestial heal on the main tank at the beginning of a battle, even if they have not taken a hit of damage yet. <br>
<br>
I have also heard of clerics casting celestial heal on the enchanter as soon as an add is detected. This seems to make happy, healthy enchanters.<br>
<br>
Being a mage, I am often the secondary source of mana for the cleric after buffs or rezzes. Cleric mana seems to be key in most cases, and we all toss mana at them when possible. Tanks often ignore the mana reports of anyone but the cleric.<br>
<br>
Group tactics in general: Strangely, I have adopted the role of &quot;secondary tank&quot; in many groups I am in. It's OK, I wear +HP gear and better AC than most mages. Now, the point I want to make in this paragraph is this: Clerics can NOT heal 6 different people at once! Heal spells take about half an hour to cast, and if the damage can not be all directed to ONE tank, then the &quot;secondary tank&quot; sort of needs to be established. <br>
<br>
Just my thoughts.<br>
<br>
Ndrokk<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/uzoldarf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zoldarf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#993300>(1/23/02 7:21:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/femarr80492frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ffshrine.com/ff1/images/chaost.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cleric tactics</span><hr size=1> Blah blah blah... just a mage you say?  You've been watching clerics work for a long time now... I think you're got a good understanding of how they operate.  Same with chanters and druids and warriors, etc.  Anyone who's played the game long enough has a pretty good grasp of how the different classes work, and can recognize the difference between good ones and excellent ones...<br>
<br>
Celestial heal is great for clerics.  Low agro, mana-efficient, etc.  However, at the higher levels, this spell becomes nearly worthless for the main tank.  They are taking damage faster than celestial heal is capable of healing.  Celestial healing is fine for healing peeps who do not have agro, but something a little more immediate is needed if they are actively taking damage from the mobs.<br>
<br>
This phenomenon was especially apparent to me on last weekend's skyfire raid.  I was regularly getting doubled for 160 damage a hit... which is far more damage than celestial healing is capable of repairing in a timely manner.  In these situations, the main tank needs to be getting complete healed.  This takes timing and preparation on the part of the cleric, and some coordination with the tank.<br>
<br>
-Zoldarf <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/uzoldarf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zoldarf</A> at: 1/23/02 7:23:02 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/ukogginnstormkoffinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kogginn Stormkoffinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fearless Leader and Webmaster</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#993300>(1/23/02 7:55:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/femarr80492frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://cofk.com/members/kogg.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cleric tactics</span><hr size=1> At Level 51, I received a spell called REMEDY. Some of you might see me use it often.  Why do I use it?  Well because it heals almost as much as superior healing, it is a 3 second cating time instead of 4.5 AND it cost less than half the mana that Superior heal does.<br>
<br>
Celestial heal is still in my lineup...  But I use uit much less frequently now that I have remedy.<br>
<br>
For example...  I pulled Kehli out of the purple the other night with remedy.  That is something that is nearly imposible to do!<br>
<br>
--- Kogginn --- <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/undrokk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ndrokk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Vice President Critterwacker</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#993300>(1/23/02 7:57:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/femarr80492frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://warmancomputers.iwarp.com/eqme.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cleric tactics (complete heal)</span><hr size=1> <br>
<br>
I enjoy watching the very clever clerics using Complete Heal.<br>
<br>
Sometimes it's more like &quot;Translocate to Bind Point in Under 10 Seconds&quot; and other times it's &quot;Cleric saves tank, and has 80% mana leftover&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
Complete is a very tricky sucker. Can a cleric predict the next 10 seconds of damage on his meat shield? If they can.... it's complete heal for you! If not... well then it's &quot;Consent me now, you're already dead&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
Styro seems to be the best complete healer I have yet seen. Perhaps that's because Styro is the tank AND the cleric!<br>
<br>
I've also seen a significant number of non-completes followed immediately with a complete, which seems to be effective in predictable damage situations. Complete healing takes SO long to cast, it also locks the cleric into a spell that he/she HAS to finish, and they are unavailable to heal other groupmates. When they are sure they have time for complete, either the battle is over, or the target is no longer taking damage, or the cleric has excellent damage forecasting skills. Any way you slice it, it's a slippery, dangerous slope with complete heal.... it works great on my earth pet though!<br>
<br>
one last point: safety before effeciency, and kudos to the clerics. I'm sure I'd have trouble with &quot;healers guilt&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
Ndrokk<br>
